What Made Node.js Special 

Node.js brought some revolutionary ideas: 

Event-driven architecture â€“ everything runs based on events. 

Non-blocking I/O â€“ it doesnâ€™t wait for one task to finish before starting the next. 

Single-threaded model â€“ one thread can handle thousands of requests efficiently through an event loop. 

This model allowed Node.js to be super fast and lightweight, perfect for real-time applications like chats, live streaming, and APIs. 

